Replace this marker with the real MAS development provisioning profile.

Required final file name:

AppleDevelopment.provisionprofile

Where it should live:

electron/build/AppleDevelopment.provisionprofile

How to create it:

1. Go to Apple Developer > Certificates, Identifiers & Profiles > Profiles.
2. Create a macOS App Development provisioning profile.
3. Select the explicit App ID: com.presenton.presenton.
4. Select the Apple Development certificate installed on the Mac.
5. Select the registered Mac device used for local testing.
6. Download the profile.
7. Rename or copy it to AppleDevelopment.provisionprofile in this folder.

Do not commit the real .provisionprofile file. It is ignored by git.
